is encourages them to craft offers that at least make sense to any likely responder. Dog and Turtle, who share valuations and both highly value blue, will see little motive to trade with each other except perhaps via small green adjustments; the most natural cross-player gains are between Parrot and either Dog or Turtle, with Parrot offloading surplus blue to get more red and Dog/Turtle doing the reverse. Over three rounds, we should see early exploratory, slightly imbalanced proposals that test whether others are willing to trade green or red, followed by one or two clearer bilateral value-creating trades where Parrot and one high-blue-value player exchange red and blue in a way that both see as clearly profitable in their private calculators. Given Dog and Parrot’s deal-readiness, it is unlikely that all nine proposal turns end in rejections; at least a couple of simple, individually beneficial trades should be agreed upon before the game ends.",
